    "description": [
        {
            "text": "Reciprocal length or inverse length is a measurement used in several branches of science and mathematics. As the reciprocal of length, common units used for this measurement include the reciprocal metre or inverse metre ($m^{-1}$), the reciprocal centimetre or inverse centimetre ($cm^{-1}$), and, in optics, the dioptre.",
